included.description:
This is where I learn to presevere. My co-founder and I tackled the following "market-product" fit:

Market = How do you get web information in a pre-G mobile world?
Product = Web Search via Text Messaging:

by:
1. Create a software platform where website results are searchable via text messaging.
2. Conduct an organic expansion that resulted in rapid increase in new customers.
3. Position Synfonic as the provider of choice for text messaging search, validated by Alexa ranking, blogs coverage, and articles in Forbes, NY Times, and other mainstream media. 

Together, Sanjay, Hans, Robert, and I took a vision and grew it to $5m valuation in Series A. This is value creation through teams in the truest sense.
included.title: Cofounder

included.description:
Provided matrix leadership across semiconductor processing, mechanical flight height, slider machining, and other functional teams and aligned supply chains in Japan, Mexico, and Philippines to ensure product can ship in a time, place and configuration ideal for serving server and desktop drive customers.

Reported to Senior Director of Advanced Technology(Adtech): 
1. Communicated clearly to all levels of engineering, manufacturing, and executive stakeholders to mitigate technical concerns, recover from delays, and scale tooling capacity and process capability to where and when they are needed, taking into account current supply as well as future consumer electronic refreshes
2. Ushered product through the entire program lifecycle - define density targets, create layered schedules, arrange manufacturing capacities, identify risks and mitigation, and explain trade-offs with analyses and recommendations to cross-functional teams
included.title: Technical Program Manager, Mobile and Server Hard Drive Heads

included.description:
Managed manufacturing and development engineering for complete transfer of 1-4 terabyte mobile  and desktop heads from NPI to manufacturing operations emphasizing bill of materials (BOMs) refinement, Cpk > 1.44 manufacturing validation, gage capable tool qualification, and capacity/utilization planning.  

Reported to Director of Manufacturing Engineering:
1. Cut cost from $8 to $3 per slider for 4 million NPI volume by employing design for manufacturability (DFM), Lean, and continuous improvement practices  that identify and eliminate the cause of discrepancies between prototype and mass production
2. Garnered 98% uptime vs 95% baseline by supporting production through multiple, concurrent, and technically complex launches by negotiating with others for needed resources to ensure product meet cost, schedule, and volume objectives
included.title: Engineering Manager, Perpendicular Recording Manufacturing

included.description:
Led process conceptualization, strategy, development, and NPI for all semiconductor processing, surface plasmon polariton materials and HAMR process analytics, managing, recruiting, and scaling 4 teams of 12 engineers, material scientists, and managers.

Reported to Senior Director of Engineering:
1. Achieved 10x signal to noise (SNR) performance and 1000x lifetime increase vs a goal of 2x SNR/10x lifetime by formulating and overseeing Agile strategy for aligning increments from design, program, operations, and characterization into sprints, then integrating development increments into low volume production.
2. Shortened a 0 to 1 million units/quarter product ramp by 1 month using scrum of scrums, feature pipelining, and cross-product process platforming that netted a concurrent launch of 4 HAMR technology and high temp. materials
included.title: Director of Engineering, Heat Assisted Magnetic Recording (HAMR)

included.description:
Lead application first product vision, strategy, roadmap, development requirements, analytics, innovations, content and product marketing of lithium ion products in tech, surveillance, construction, advertising, and other emerging markets. 

Report to CEO:
1. Win Tesla, Google, and apple as multi-year, $20,000/year, long term lease customer by ensuring product meet power consumption, recharge rate, and other current and emerging needs of remote service providers and IoT/edge application developers
2. Increase revenue by 10% to $1,000,000+ with new surveillance, radar, and charging business models by delivering breakthrough messaging, built go-to market strategy, ran customer-focused marketing program, and crafted compelling content (customer success stories, brochures, presentations, demos, how to guides etc.) that generate brand awareness and leads in US, Canada, and Mexico
3. Reduce product ship time from 2 to 1.5 month by running daily scrums that review local stakeholder design, demo to improve efficiency and quality of product development, and align Chinese OEM/ODM outputs with supply chain milestones
4. Develop new Agile product practices and process that improve product functionality through in-depth buyer persona and journey mapping, funnel analysis, product measurement and regression, A/B test and trending prediction, and concept review
